list_definition.definition: (often seagull) a type of web-footed sea bird, usually black and white or grey and white.

list_ex_of_english: The observations of ivory gulls at sea presented here are consistent with this.
These observations suggest that ivory gulls are not as opportunistic as other gulls.
The ivory gulls observed could have been breeders feeding at sea, failed breeders, or non-breeding birds.
A few scattered gulls are found to feed particularly on the smaller snails available.
All ivory gulls were observed in small areas of open water in large expanses covered with mostly solid sea ice.
The gull could not reply to that, and so the raven had won.
The authors saw a total of 74 ivory gulls in 1993 and 17 in 2002.
In this context, ivory gulls were loafing on ice pack at the edge of openings.
